   833 				;==========================================================================
   834 				; FSUB [DA60]	Subtract FR1 from FR0; FR1 is altered
   835 				; FADD [DA66]	Add FR1 to FR0; FR1 is altered
   836 				;
   837 				; Add or subtract two numbers. When denormalizing the smaller number, any
   838 				; precision shifted out is dropped by truncation instead of rounding.
   839 				; For instance, 1.23456788 + 0.000000019 = 1.23456789 and not 1.23456790.
   840 				;
   841 				; Quirks:
   842 				;	- FADD must be able to handle negative zeroes for either FR0 or FR1.
   843 				;	  FR1 falls out of the address of FSUB, since the most obvious
   844 				;	  implementation is to negate the FR1 sign. FR0 is possible via
   845 				;	  VAL("-0") in BASIC.
   846 				;
   847 DA5F					fixadr	$da60
Macro: FIXADR [Source: source/Shared/mathpack.s]
