   967 				; FMUL [DADB]:	Multiply FR0 * FR1 -> FR0; FR1 modified
   968 				;
   969 				; Multiply two floating point numbers.
   970 				;
   971 				; FMUL generates and accumulates full partial products, so intermediate
   972 				; results produce the full 19 significant digits, but the result is then
   973 				; truncated without rounding back to 10 significant digits.
   974 				;
   975 DAD6				fixadr	$dad8
