  1923 				;==========================================================================
  1924 				; LOG [DECD]	Compute ln x
  1925 				; LOG10 [DED1]	Compute log10 x
  1926 				;
  1927 				; The algorithm is from Ruckdeschel, Table VI.11, page 173:
  1928 				;
  1929 				;	LOG10(X) = 0.5 + A1*Z + A2*Z^3 + ... + A10*Z^19
  1930 				;		where Z = (X - c) / (X + c) where c - 3.162277660
  1931 				;		for 1 <= X <= 10 [sic].
  1932 				;
  1933 				; The constant c is sqrt(10). The exponent of the input number is removed
  1934 				; and the mantissa divided by 10 if needed to reduce range to [1, 10).
  1935 				;
  1936 				; LOG(x) is computed by dividing LOG10(x) by LOG10(e). It would be faster
  1937 				; to multiply by the reciprocal instead, but the division needs to be done
  1938 				; to match results.
  1939 				;
  1940 DEC9				fixadr	$decd
